cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on database systems and their performance in main memory multi-core environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses algorithmic and control techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses performance scaling, which could place it in cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper discusses parallel query engines, which could place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages).
